                <h1>Muhammad: The Life and Legacy of the Prophet</h1>
                <p>Muhammad, the founder of Islam, is a pivotal figure in world history. Born in Mecca around 570 CE, he received revelations that formed the Quran, guiding millions. As a prophet and leader, he emphasized compassion, justice, and community. His teachings continue to influence the spiritual and moral compass of billions worldwide.</p>
